Incident.Summary: Concerning text on a youtube video. Cybertip #181201647

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Attachments: -CyberTip #181201647 Narrative: On December 20, 2023, the Maryland State Police Technical Investigation Section / Maryland Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force (MD ICAC) received National Center for Missing and Exploited Children (NCMEC) Cyber-Tipline report #181201647. This CyberTip was initially reported to NCMEC by Google, indicating that a subject uploading/possessing/distributing child pornography on the internet. After deconfliction of the reported identifiers and a review of the content, based upon the volume of NCMEC referrals to the MD ICAC and other factors, the determination was made to administratively document this CyberTip referral pending additional information. The CyberTip is attached to this report as reference, and the relevant suspect information is incorporated below: SUSPECT INFORMATION: URL: text-decoration:underline">http://youtube.com/watch%3Fv%3DTOyL4UTYLd8%26lc%3DUgx7354Sr5eRliS4_Rd4AaABAg Name: Isaiah Black Mobile Phone: +13018754592 (Verified 09-07-2023 01:20:13 UTC) Date of Birth: 03-18-1999 Email Address: haljake85@gmail.com (Verified) Email Address: text-decoration:underline">basketballgod45674@gmail.com TFC Burnett reviewed this CyberTip and observed it to contain the below reported comment: Google became aware of this communication: Comment Text: How to get child porn? We are reporting a comment found on the YouTube platform with the above text. The comment was discovered at the URL we have description. Video Title: The City of PED0PHILES Video Description: DISCLAIMER: This video is for educational and documentary purposes only. It contains material that may be disturbing or offensive to some viewers, but it is presented in a truthful and non-exploitative manner. The views expressed in this video do not necessarily reflect the views of the creator or YouTube. TFC Burnett conducted a search of the reported IP address (2600:4040:2e07:5300:94be:79da:d032:8b4c) which is registered through Verizon Fios and geo-locates to Laurel, MD. Based on the lack of evidence for a specific crime, this incident report is administratively closed pending additional information. Case Status CLOSED / POLICE INFORMATION
